Cell.Text: My story, huh? Everyone in Cidhna Mine has a tale. Let's hear yours first. When was the first time you felt chains around your wrists?

Node.Caption: MS02BraigreStoryTopic: Madanach asked me to hear your story.

Cell.Text: So know what it's like to have your life in someone else's hands. Why should they get to decide? Isn't judgment for the gods?

Node.Caption: MS02BraigreTopic01: It was in Helgen. I was being sent to the executioner.

Cell.Text: Then you know the hard looks as judgment gets set upon you. The sneers of people who never had to face sentence.

Node.Caption: MS02BraigreTopic02: Young. I've always been known to get into trouble.

Cell.Text: Fine. Don't tell me. But I know that look in your eyes. Someone who's faced death at the hands of the law.
Do you have any family? Anyone waiting for you on the outside?

[S] <<Shared>> I had a daughter, once. She'd be 23 this year. Married to some hot-headed silver worker or maybe on her own learning the herb trade. | The Nords didn't care who was and who wasn't involved in the Forsworn Uprising. I had spoken to Madanach once, that was enough. | But my little Aethra didn't want to see her papa leave her. She pleaded to the Jarl to take her instead. | And after they made me watch as her head rolled off the block, they threw me in here anyway, to dig up their silver.

Node.Caption: MS02BraigreTopic04: Yes, but they're far from Skyrim.

Node.Caption: MS02BraigTopic06: None that I care to talk about.

Cell.Text: My daughter is the one who needs your pity. I'm just a poor Forsworn whose only regret is not killing more Nords before I was locked up.

Node.Caption: MS02BraigSorryTopic: I'm sorry to hear what happened to you.

Cell.Text: I'm not Madanach. I was never a leader of the Forsworn. The only anger I can justify is my own. | But every family in the Reach has a story like mine. There are no innocent onlookers in this struggle. Just the guilty, and the dead.

Node.Caption: MS02BraigForswornTopic: You think your story justifies the murders the Forsworn have committed?
